# Public Repository Marker
#
# This file signals that one or more remotes point to a public hosting
# service (e.g., GitHub public repo). When present, the pre-commit hook
# blocks direct `git commit` and requires using `scripts/verified-commit.sh`
# after reviewing the diff for sensitive or environment-specific content.
#
# LAN-only remotes (e.g., private Gitea) do not count as public.
#
# To disable: delete this file. This is an intentional action -- you are
# accepting responsibility for ensuring no PII or infra details leak.
#
# Created by: python scripts/setup.py (or manually)
